Bedford Avenue, north side, from Clymer Street to Taylor S reet, looking east. At the corner of the former Streey is the old First Dutch Reforhed Church of Williamisbura, which later became a synagogue. '  3A9E shows the 3-story house adjoining thekhurch, known as the Cross mansion and owned by Harion Cross, whose father settled in Brooklyn in 1845. EAE1 is west from Taylor Str et, showing the aforementionec sturctures an the Hebrew High School (right). In the left backgrouno is the
Christ Protestant Epdscopal Church.
